# Linux

1) Create and activate virtual python3 environment using version <= 3.11
python3.11 -m venv myenv
source venv/bin/activate

2) Install requirements
pip install -r requirements.txt

3) Optional: If you wish to use PTMCMCSampler (use_pt=True in example.py), you may want to use mpi4py
pip install mpi4py

Note: This requires python-devel and mpi packages that can be installed in Fedora using:
sudo dnf install mpich-devel
sudo dnf install openmpi-devel
sudo dnf install python3.11-devel

3) Adopt and run example.py for your project

